Motorists have been advised to find alternative routes on Friday morning as traffic has been heavily affected. JOHANNESBURG - Thirteen people have been injured in a crash on Grayston Drive in Sandton, with two people in a critical condition. It’s understood that a taxi and truck collided on the bridge on Friday morning. JMPD’S Wayne Minnaar says: “It’s alleged that the taxi skipped a red light, however, further investigation will be done.” Motorists have been advised to find alternative routes on Friday morning as traffic has been heavily affected. 